FBIS4-54642 "dreeu085_i_94011" FBIS-EEU-94-085 Daily Report 2 May 1994 BOSNIA-HERZEGOVINA UNPROFOR General Complains of Serbian Harassment UNPROFOR General Complains of Serbian Harassment LD0205203094 Paris TF-1 Television Network in French 1800 GMT 2 May 94 LD0205203094 Paris TF-1 Television Network French BFN [Excerpts] The situation is once more worrying in Bosnia, particularly in Sarajevo and around Gorazde too where a UN Protection Forces [UNPROFOR] convoy is blocked by Serbs. This incident is reported to be very serious. Incidents are more and more frequent and cease-fires are no longer respected. [passage omitted] [Begin recording] [Brigadier General Andre Soubirou, captioned as UNPROFOR commander for Sarajevo sector] I have been hindered since the start of the Gorazde crisis. Our freedom of movement has been restricted. The tension provoked by the Gorazde crisis resulted in massive harassment by the Serb side. There were attempts to get more weapons through our sector by taking advantage of these difficulties. [end recording] [passage omitted]
